  "text": "It is known that in some cases the underlying geometry in lattice-based models can have a significant effect on the results obtained from a microscopic point of view. For example in a different context, at the level of the universality of phase transitions in equilibrium systems, some differences were found numerically between square and triangular lattices [CITATION_1] and later predicted theoretically [CITATION_2] . Here, we use the quantum Hamiltonian formalism to calculate the RF of the global current in the two geometries shown in Fig. 1 and thus investigate the influence of the lattice on the dynamical properties of the ZRP.",
